{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7a5d2de5-3176-4a79-b660-e45a932b5f73","content":"No worries — I don't need to see the project to answer this. Here's how to configure it:\n\nCreate **`.vscode/mcp.json`** in your workspace root:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"servers\": {\n    \"my-mcp-server\": {\n      \"type\": \"stdio\",\n      \"command\": \"dotnet\",\n      \"args\": [\"run\", \"--project\", \"src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **`type: \"stdio\"`** — Copilot communicates with your server over stdin/stdout.\n- Your server must use the **stdio transport** (not HTTP/SSE). If you're using the `ModelContextProtocol` NuGet package, that's `UseStdioServerTransport()`.\n- Make sure your server does **not** write logs to stdout — use stderr instead, or Copilot will fail to parse responses.\n- After saving, open the **Command Palette → \"MCP: List Servers\"** to verify it's detected.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bd0f2d69-39f2-431a-a367-00ebb8f11835","outputTokens":257},"id":"91a675f7-d676-4ab1-bbfe-ac9e9571fb85","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:51:45.192Z","parentId":"52229f62-ad09-467e-b0ca-c75d5cccb608"}
